### Variables — change these as you test
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000
@accessToken = paste_your_access_token_here_after_login

### =====================
### AUTH
### =====================

### Register
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Delightsome",
  "username": "nonny",
  "email": "delightofili0@gmail.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "nonso@gmail.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Refresh token
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

### Logout
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/logout
Content-Type: application/json

### Forgot password
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "nonso@gmail.com"
}

### Reset password
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/reset-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "paste_token_from_email_here",
  "password": "newpassword123"
}

### Verify email
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/verify-email?token=paste_token_here

### =====================
### LINKS
### =====================

### Get all links
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/links

### Get all links with filter
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/links?category=tools&page=1

### Get single link
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/links/1

### Create a link (requires auth)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/links
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

{
  "title": "MDN Web Docs",
  "url": "https://developer.mozilla.org",
  "category": "tools",
  "description": "The best web documentation"
}

### Update a link (requires auth + ownership)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/links/1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

{
  "title": "MDN Web Docs Updated"
}

### Delete a link (requires auth + ownership)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/links/1
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Upvote a link (requires auth)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/links/1/upvote
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Export links as CSV
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/links/export
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### =====================
### USERS
### =====================

### Upload avatar (requires auth)
### For file uploads REST Client uses a different syntax
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users/avatar
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----boundary

------boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="avatar"; filename="photo.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< ./test.jpg
------boundary--

### =====================
### NOTIFICATIONS
### =====================

### Get all notifications
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/notifications
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Get unread count
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/notifications/count
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Mark all as read
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/notifications/read
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}